div.p:
The formal definition for the msDescription element is as
follows:

&msDescription;

The additional phrase-level elements are formally defined as follows:

&catchwords;
&dimensions;
&height;
&depth;
&width;
&heraldry;
&locus;
&material;
&origDate;
&origPlace;
&secFol;
&signatures;
&stamp;
&watermark;

The msIdentifier element and its constituents are formally
defined as follows:

&msIdentifier;
&institution;
&repository;
&collection;
&altIdentifier;
&msName;

The msContents element and its constituents are formally defined as follows:

&colophon;
&explicit;
&filiation;
&finalRubric;
&incipit;
&msContents;
&msItem;
&msItemStruct;
&rubric;
&summary;
&textLang;

This module defines one additional class, of which
msContents and some of its constituents are members:

  &att.msExcerpt;

The formal definition for the physDesc element and its
constituents is as follows:

&physDesc;
&objectDesc;
&supportDesc;
&support;
&collation;
&foliation;
&condition;
&layoutDesc;
&layout;
&handDesc;
&handNote;
&musicNotation;
&decoDesc;
&decoNote;
&additions;
&bindingDesc;
&binding;
&sealDesc;
&seal;
&accMat;

The history element and its immediate component elements
are formally defined as follows:

&history;
&origin;
&provenance;
&acquisition;

The adminInfo element and its immediate component elements
are formally defined as follows:

&adminInfo;
&recordHist;
&source;

&custodialHist;
&custEvent;
